-- Turkish 12-Month Inflation Expectations Increase in Central Bank's Survey
-- Steve Bryant
-- 2010-06-22T13:31:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-22/turkish-12-month-inflation-expectations-increase-in-central-bank-s-survey.html

          
          
             Turkish estimates for inflation in
12 months time rose to 7.35 percent from 7.23 percent, the
central bank said in a biweekly survey.  
 Predictions for inflation at the end of this year fell to
8.01 percent from 8.1 percent, according to the survey of
economists and businessmen published by the central bank in
Ankara today.  
 Turkish economic growth this year was foreseen at 5.2
percent compared with a previous estimate of 5.1 percent, the
bank said.  
